Description: The Pokemon saga continues with the introduction of two new trainers: Black and White.
Title: POKEMON BLACK AND WHITE, VOL. 4
Author: Hidenori Kusaka

Description: A predecessor to "Sailor Moon," this collection of stories has never before been printed in the United States.
Title: CODENAME: SAILOR V, Vol. 1
Author: Naoko Takeuchi

Description: The incredibly popular manga series that spawned an anime series, stage musicals and countless imitators gets a new printing.
Title: SAILOR MOON, VOL. 1
Author: Naoko Takeuchi

Description: Sebastian is a loyal butler who moves easily from dinner parties to the underworld. Is he too good to be true? Is he even human? In this volume: children are missing and Queen Victoria is not happy.
Title: BLACK BUTLER, VOL. 7
Author: Yana Toboso

Description: Sakura Mamiya is haunted by her ability to see dead people. Her classmate, Rinne Rokudo, can help but only for the right price.
Title: RIN-NE, VOL. 7
Author: Rumiko Takahashi

Description: A young princess named Sapphire must pretend to be male in order to inherit the throne. By the godfather of manga.
Title: PRINCESS KNIGHT, VOL. 1
Author: Osamu Tezuka

Description: Misao Harada can see into a magical realm where she is the bride demon of prophecy.
Title: BLACK BIRD, VOL. 11
Author: Kanoko Sakurakoji

Description: Maka, an arms expert, wants to turn the Soul Eater, her living scythe, into the ultimate weapon for Death.
Title: SOUL EATER, VOL. 7
Author: Atsushi Ohkubo

Description: In a dark future, four individuals come together and journey to a mysterious "underground" running beneath the city on a quest for answers.
Title: DOGS, VOL. 6
Author: Shirow Miwa

Description: 15-year-old Allen Walker roams the earth searching for "Innocence," the material used to create weapons that can destroy demons that this fictional version of 19th century England.
Title: D. GRAY-MAN, VOL. 21
Author: Katsura Hoshino
